<seg id=1> Fei Xiaotong Wins Magsaysay Award </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Manila, Aug. 31 (Xiong Changyi reporting): Professor Fei Xiaotong, China's renowned sociologist and vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, received the Magsaysay "Community Leader" Award for 1994 here this afternoon. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The awards ceremony was held in the Philippine Cultural Center. </seg>
<seg id=4> Philippine president Ramos attended the ceremony and presented the six recipients of the Magsaysay awards with medals, prizes and certificates. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Expressing his thanks, Fei Xiaotong said, "I will definitely not fail to live up to this encouragement from you, our good neighbors. No matter how many years and months are allotted me, I will definitely be conscientious and do my best to make use of every moment, to exert all my energies to doing effective, good things for the people of Asia, and even for the people of the world. I will work to make the accumulated knowledge of humanity function as a means of promoting better societal development." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The award is named for the former president of the Philippines, Ramon Magsaysay, and has been called the Asian Nobel Prize. </seg>
<seg id=7> There are five awards in given out every year in the following categories: government service, community leadership, news, literature and creative communications, and exceptional contributions made by international individuals or organizations. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The awards have been given out since 1958, with 172 individuals and 14 organizations as recipients. </seg>
</p>
